President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. Elizabeth M. Harman is nominated for Assistant Administrator of the Federal Emergency Management Agency (Grant Programs) at the Department of Homeland Security. Harman has experience as a former firefighter and paramedic and currently serves as the director of the Hazardous Materials and Weapons of Mass Destruction Training Department at the International Association of Fire Fighters. George Apostolakis is nominated for Commissioner of the Nuclear Regulatory Commission. He is a professor at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology and has expertise in nuclear science and engineering. William D. Magwood, IV is also nominated for Commissioner of the Nuclear Regulatory Commission. He previously served as the longest-serving head of the United States' civilian nuclear technology program and founded Advanced Energy Strategies. Peter A. Prahar is nominated for Ambassador to the Federated States of Micronesia. He currently serves as the Transnational Crime Officer at the U.S. Embassy in Moscow. Eleni Tsakopoulos-Kounalakis is nominated for Ambassador to the Republic of Hungary. She is a businesswoman, civic leader, and philanthropist, and has served as president of AKT Development Corporation.